   New Regulations Will Result in Changes in OHV Program
   The Office of Administrative Law determined on December 1, 1998 that
   the OHV Grant Program was using underground regulations to administer
   the Grant Program. Underground regulations are rules and policies that
   are developed by a State Agency that affect the general population of
   California, but the Divisions legal counsel advised that the OHV Grant
   Program could not continue until the Division had changed the rules and
   policies into regulations. (continued)
   [spacer.gif] [wedge.gif] New Regulations Will Result in Changes in OHV
   Grant Program

   Doing the Right Thing with Your Used Motor oil
   Find out what CIWMB is, why CIWMB care about motor oil recycling, why
   the popularity of recycling is growing, why OHVers care about the
   environment, giving re-refined motor oil a try, and tips on proper
   handling of used motor oil and filters.
